ed the choices of generals, the fates of communities, and the trajectory of environmental change in North China"--cProvided by publisher.0 aPrint version record.  a44 0aSino-Japanese War, 1937-1945xEnvironmental aspectszChinazHenan Sheng. 0aSino-Japanese War, 1937-1945xEnvironmental aspectszChinazYellow River. 0aSino-Japanese War, 1937-1945xRefugees. 0aEnvironmental degradationzChinazHenan ShengxHistoryy20th century. 0aNaturexEffect of human beings onzChinazHenan ShengxHistoryy20th century. 0aHenan Sheng (China)xHistory, Militaryy20th century. 0aHenan Sheng (China)xEnvironmental conditions. 0aYellow River (China)xHistory, Militaryy20th century. 0aYellow River (China)xEnvironmental conditions. 0aStudies in environment and history.403University of Alberta Accessuhttp://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=true&scope=site&db=nlebk&db=nlabk&AN=919787xLimited to 365 Uses Per Calendar Yearz(Unlimited Concurrent Users)  wORDERhUAINzPDACOUTTS  aInternet AccesswLCc1i6783807-1001lINTERNETmUAINTERNETrYsYtE-RESOURCEu1/16/2015xE-BOOKzPDAOWNED01ahttp://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n2009042246bhttp://viaf.org/viaf/91035757